title: Westminster logo face
author: truoc

comments.content: Hi, I would greatly appreciate if anyone would be able to identify this typeface.

After further inspection of [The Westminster Roppongi website](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317063136/http:/www.tw-r.jp/), I'm pretty convinced it's [Circe](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317063136/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/paratype/circe) using the alternate four upper terminals / [W](http://web.archive.org/web/20150317063136/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/paratype/circe/extra-light/glyphs.html#glyphs/510306/1261).

Good find Ryuk. With \_w/W\_ in fifty-five variations Circe might be the record holder!  
Don
Thanks for your help Ryuk, appreciate it.
